text: Morwincha is a locality in the Scenic Rim Region, Queensland, Australia. ==Census Data== Morwincha has a population of 30 at the . The locality contains 14 households, in which 51.6% of the population are males and 48.4% of the population are females with a median age of 50, 12 years above the national average. The average weekly household income is $899, $539 below the national average. == References == Category:Scenic Rim Region Category:Localities in Queensland
